<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="450" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Señor
                                <persName type="to">Hurtado</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-10"><hi rend="italic">October 10,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="italic">My dear</hi> Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurtado</hi>:</p>
                    <p>If convenient to you, I shall be greatly obliged if you will call at the
                        Department to-morrow, Wednesday, the 11th instant, any time between 10 and
                        11 o’clock in the morning, for a conference in relation to your note of
                        October 5, 1893.</p>
                    <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>